WEB API

Recipe Web Application 
This is a simple web application that allows users to search for food recipes and allow users to add to favorites.
This application is built using React, Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and Axios. Below will be list out the npm that needs to be installed.

To run this project locally:
1. First you need to create react app using npx create-react-app my-react-app.
2. After creating the react project you can drag the src folder to the react project
3. Next you can add a folder in public which is called images and add those image to the images folder.
4. Next add the server.js to the folder
5. Package.json is for you to refer to what dependencies I have installed.

Step to do Before starting to run the project:
1. Make sure you change the mongoURI to your MongoDb URI in server.js.
const mongoURI =
  "mongodb+srv://jiade:testing123@clusterreact.easjxty.mongodb.net/webapi?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=ClusterReact";
2. Install all the dependencies.
-npm i axios bootstrap cors express mongoose nodemon react-bootsrap react-router-dom

3. Run node server.js in the terminal to connect the database

4. npm start


